  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Shutdown dose rate was analyzed to consider a maintenance progress for DEMO by using MCNP-5 and DCHAIN-SP2001. • The dose rate of pipe cutting and re-welding points in the maintenance ports were as low as 0.01 Gy/h for blanket segment and 0.1 Gy/h for divertor cassette. • In terms of spatial dose rate, the maintenance scheme for ITER, such as pipe cutting and re-welding, is applicable also to DEMO.</subfield>
